data.title: TROJ_KULUOZ.WSBR - Threat Encyclopedia
data.meta_description: This Trojan  arrives on a system as a file dropped by other malware or as a file downloaded unknowingly by users when visiting malicious sites.
data.text:
Arrival Details

This Trojan arrives on a system as a file dropped by other malware or as a file downloaded unknowingly by users when visiting malicious sites.

Autostart Technique

This Trojan adds the following registry entries to enable its automatic execution at every system startup:

HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\

Windows\CurrentVersion\Run

nhhrpiim = "%Application Data%\bvraeqjj.exe "

Other System Modifications

This Trojan adds the following registry keys:

HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\pmqddmcn

It adds the following registry entries:

HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\pmqddmcn

wdsenmaf = "{random values}"

Dropping Routine

This Trojan drops the following files:

%Application Data%\bvraeqjj.exe

(Note: %Application Data% is the current user's Application Data folder, which is usually C:\Documents and Settings\{user name}\Application Data on Windows 2000, XP, and Server 2003, or C:\Users\{user name}\AppData\Roaming on Windows Vista and 7.)
